				</common:classification>
			</classificationInformation>
			<common:generalComment xml:lang="en">Alumina, also known as the oxide of aluminum, occurs both in pure form as corundum and in hydrated forms (as in bauxite). It is widely used in a variety of industrial abrasive materials due to its superior hardness and strength. Alumina can also be used as a coating to protect against abrasion and in refractory products due to its high melting point. In most industrial applications, corundum has been replaced by synthetic materials such as alumina, an aluminum oxide made from bauxite.</common:generalComment>
			<common:generalComment xml:lang="zh">氧化铝又称铝的氧化物，以刚玉和水合形式（如铝土矿）存在。由于其硬度和强度极高，氧化铝被广泛用于各种工业研磨材料。氧化铝还可用作涂层以防止磨损，并因其熔点高而用于耐火产品。在大多数工业应用中，刚玉已被氧化铝等合成材料所取代，氧化铝是从铝土矿中提取的一种氧化铝。</common:generalComment>
			<sumFormula>Al2O3</sumFormula>
